        print "<b>Global Settings:</b> <br><br>Global Settings for all Modules. <br>-Min clockins seconds between 2 clockin for same Employee ( ideal = 30 seconds): If an Employee clocks continously more than once by mistake or deliberately, the extra clockings would effect his Attendance for the Day and will lead to wrong or NO Attendance calculations. The System ignores all clockings on all Terminals within the Time (in seconds) specified here after his first clocking on the Unit. <br>- Max Out Time (HHMM) for Night Staff: For Night Shift Scenarios, a Cut Off Time (Day Change Over Time for Night Shift) is specified here which reflects that All employees doing Night Shift as of yesterday have definitely closed and No Employee to do Night Shift today has yet resumed duty. <br>- Use Projects: Projects can be used to allocate the Time spent in exact Man Hours to each Project. A summary of Total Time spent on each Project can then be formulated for review. <br>- Use Exit Terminals: In case of Sites with a Big Premise, it is good to monitor the movement of the Employees between the Premise Gate and their Department. Terminals are installed at the Main Gates of the Premise which are used to ONLY Record and Display Time of Exit/ Entry and Department Terminals are used to compute the Working Time. This feature helps in actually monitoring the time spent by an Employee loitering around in the Campus. Also, it can be used to RESTRICT entries of un wanted elements in the Premises <br>- Allow NON-CLOCKING on Exit Terminal: By setting this Option to Yes, the System will calculate the Employee's Attendance even if there is NO clocking on the defined Exit Terminals. Department Terminal Clockings are anywayz a compulsion. <br>- Use Shift Rotation: Setting this option to YES, enables the Shift Rotation Menu. Shift can be scheduled to rotate once a week from Scheduled Task. <br>- Next Shift Rotation Date (Edit this Field ONLY if you have RUN the Shift Rotation Process manually): Everytime the Shift Rotates, this field is being updated by a date which is 7 days later. <br>Pay EARLY IN Overtime: Enabling this Option entitles Employees to receive OT before for resuming before their Resume Time <br>- Pay EARLY IN Overtime on OT Days/Dates: Although, OT before the Schedule Time may NOT be paid on Normal Days, but there may be a need to pay Early IN Overtime on weekends or public holidays depending on the nature of the work. This option can be set YES or NO accordingly <br>- Pay LESS LUNCH Overtime: For Employees Clocking for Break, if this Option is set to YES, the System pays OT for the time NOT consimed for break <br>- Allow NO-BREAK (If Shift Type uses BREAK): For Shifts with Break Clocking options, if this option is set to YES, Attendance is NOT processed if the System DOES NOT find the Break IN and Break OUT clockings <br>- Rename Social No Column to (Max Length: 5): Social No column is an additional provisional Column in the Database which can be custom labelled in all Reports <br>- Minutes Value (after Grace Time) for Late Arrival Report: Takes this as a default value for generating Late Arrival Report. <br>- Database Backup Path (Remove Trailing Backslash '\\'): It is a mandate to schedule regular backup of the Database. Specify a path to the folder where the Database is to be thrown to. Preferably, use an external USB drive for Backup <br>Transaction Record Lock/ Migration Date: In case, you are migrating Time and Attendance Results to Payroll, ensure to put a lock date here. The System will NOT allow any ammendments on any Transaction ON or BEFORE this date - Clicking the <b>Change</b> button enables to change the Date alone. Deletion rights on this Module enables the functionality of this button. - If your System is pre configured to migrate the Time and Attendance Database to any other System, click the <b>Execute DB Migrate</b> button to execute the same. <br>-SMTP SERVER: If you wish to use the Report Mailer Option, please specify the SMTP Server Name or IP Address to be used to send Emails. Mails would be sent to the Email Addresses specified for each user in the User Management Module. Mails will be sent ONLY to Users with enabled DELETE option on General Reports <br>FROM  EMAIL ADDRESS: Should exist on the Email Server <br>SMTP USERNAME: For Outgoing SMTP Authentication <br>SMTP PASSWORD: For Outgoing SMTP Authentication <br>- Include Selected Flags for the TOTAL Days Column Calculation for Snapshot Report: Some Days can be marked with Flags as <b>SUSPENSION</b>. This Days just NEED to show but NOT to be calculated in Attendance. Such Flags can be un checked from this List. <br>Flag Titles: A General Notification of Titles for each Flag Ex: Violet = Sick Leave, Purple = Public Holiday <br>- Click <b>Save Changes</b> to save the Records <br>- Use <b>Upload Employee Info</b> button to update Employee Details from an XML File";
        break;
